==English==
'''thumb one's nose'''

===Verb===
# (''literally'') to place a [[thumb]] upon the [[nose]] in a [[gesture]] of mild disrespect
#:''My brother thumbed his nose in reply to my snide remarks.''
# (''figuratively'') to act [[disrespect]]fully, especially by [[flout]]ing the object of disrespect
#:''[[w:Richard_Feynman|Richard Feynman]] delighted in thumbing his nose at bureaucracy.''

